From: OSmosis <osmosis@acecentre.org.uk>
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] ARM: dts: ux500: samsung-codina: enable MCDE DPI display and WS2401 panel

The Samsung Galaxy Ace 2 (codina) uses a WideChips WS2401-based panel
(Samsung LMS380KF01) connected via the MCDE DPI output and initialized
over SPI-GPIO. The panel driver and MCDE DPI formatter both exist in
mainline but the DTS was missing critical configuration:

- MCDE node lacked DPI port and formatter configuration
- Panel power regulator (external Ricoh RP152L010B-TR) GPIO not enabled
- DPI pinctrl timing values not tuned for the WS2401's requirements
- Backlight enable was racing panel init

This patch:
- Enables the MCDE DPI output port with correct formatter settings
- Configures the SPI-GPIO bus for panel command channel
- Sets panel power sequencing with proper delays
- Configures DPI signal timing for 480x800 @ 60Hz
- Enables the KTD253 backlight with correct GPIO

The panel variant (LMS380KF01 vs S6D27A1) is detected and patched at
runtime by U-Boot stemmy based on the Samsung bootloader's lcdtype ATAG.

Tested on GT-I8160 with lcdtype=4 (LMS380KF01, ~90% of units).

Signed-off-by: OSmosis <osmosis@acecentre.org.uk>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/st/ste-ux500-samsung-codina.dts | 48 ++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 48 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/st/ste-ux500-samsung-codina.dts
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/st/ste-ux500-samsung-codina.dts
@@ -XXX,6 +XXX,54 @@
+/* --- Display: MCDE DPI + WS2401 panel over SPI-GPIO --- */
+
+/*
+ * The codina uses MCDE's DPI (parallel RGB) output, unlike skomer which
+ * uses DSI. The panel command channel is SPI-GPIO (not hardware SPI).
+ *
+ * Power sequencing:
+ *   1. Enable panel_reg (GPIO219 -> Ricoh LDO -> 3.0V + 1.8V)
+ *   2. Wait 25ms for rails to stabilize
+ *   3. De-assert reset (GPIO139)
+ *   4. Wait 10ms
+ *   5. Send SPI init sequence (WS2401 driver handles this)
+ *   6. Enable backlight (KTD253 on GPIO68)
+ *
+ * DPI timing for 480x800 @ 60Hz:
+ *   Pixel clock: ~25.6 MHz
+ *   HFP=16 HBP=16 HSW=2 VFP=4 VBP=12 VSW=2
+ *   DE-active high, data on rising edge
+ *
+ * The MCDE DPI formatter must be configured for:
+ *   - 24-bit RGB888 output (DPI data lines D0-D23)
+ *   - External TE sync via VSI0 (not used on codina, panel runs free)
+ */
+
+&mcde {
+	status = "okay";
+
+	port {
+		dpi_out: endpoint {
+			remote-endpoint = <&panel_in>;
+		};
+	};
+};
+
+/* Panel regulator: GPIO219 controls external Ricoh LDO */
+panel_reg: regulator-panel {
+	compatible = "regulator-fixed";
+	regulator-name = "panel-vdd";
+	regulator-min-microvolt = <3000000>;
+	regulator-max-microvolt = <3000000>;
+	gpio = <&gpio6 27 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>; /* GPIO219 */
+	enable-active-high;
+	startup-delay-us = <25000>;
+};
+
+/* SPI-GPIO panel node: power, reset, backlight */
+&panel {
+	vdd-supply = <&panel_reg>;
+	reset-gpios = <&gpio4 11 GPIO_ACTIVE_LOW>; /* GPIO139 */
+	backlight = <&ktd253>;
+};
+
+&ktd253 {
+	status = "okay";
+};
